<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Web Development Quick-Reference</title>
    <!-- Linking an external stylesheet -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Web Tech Guide</h1>
        <p>A reference for tags and styles covered in Chapter 2 and 4.</p>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>Text Formatting Tags</h2>
            <p>Use <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code> for <strong>bold</strong> and <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> for <em>italics</em>.</p>
            
            <h3>Code Snippets</h3>
            <p>Use the <code>&lt;pre&gt;</code> tag to preserve whitespace for code blocks:</p>
            <pre>
function helloWorld() {
    console.log("Hello, IT Student!");
}
            </pre>

            <h3>Quotes and Time</h3>
            <p>The <code>&lt;blockquote&gt;</code> is for long quotes, and <code>&lt;time&gt;</code> defines a specific date.</p>
            <p>Current Date: <time datetime="2026-04-29">April 29, 2026</time></p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2026 Web Development Module</p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
